article.title: Automorphism groups of superspecial curves of genus $4$ over $\mathbb F_{11}$

multiple_choice_question.text: Which of the following superspecial curves has an automorphism group isomorphic to D<sub>4</sub> over F<sub>11</sub>?
What is the order of the automorphism group of the superspecial curve C<sup>(Dege)</sup><sub>9</sub> over F<sub>11</sub>?
What does the formula  O˜<sub>ϕ</sub>(K) = A T˜ UWU˜  represent?
choices: The Jacobian of a superspecial curve
The Bruhat decomposition of the orthogonal similitude group
The mass formula for superspecial abelian varieties
The isomorphism class of a nonhyperelliptic curve

multiple_choice_question.text: What does the formula H<sup>1</sup>(Γ, Aut(C)) ≃ Aut(C)/σ-conjugacy  describe?
choices: The structure of the dihedral group D<sub>6</sub>
The F<sub>11</sub>-isomorphism classes of nonhyperelliptic superspecial curves
The parametrization of F<sub>11</sub>-forms of a superspecial curve C using Galois cohomology
The computation of the σ-stabilizer group of an element in Aut(C)
